WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:09.111
I would like to call your attention this evening to verses 25, 26, and 27 in the 11th chapter of Paul's Epistle to the Romans.

00:10.011 --> 00:14.055
Or I would not brethren that he should be ignorant of this mystery.

00:14.095 --> 00:17.859
Last ye should be wise in your own conceits.

00:18.580 --> 00:25.486
The blindness in part has happened to Israel until the fullness of the Gentiles become in.

00:26.407 --> 00:29.650
And so all Israel shall be saved.

00:30.050 --> 00:37.438
As it is written, there shall come out of Zion the deliverer, and shall turn away on godliness from Jacob.

00:38.199 --> 00:44.846
For this is my covenant unto them, when I shall take away their sin."

00:44.866 --> 00:59.442
Now, we are looking at this great statement contained here, and which I have already described to you as the apostles' way of expressing his absolute certainty about the

00:59.778 --> 01:07.630
restoration of the Jews to the Kingdom of God and to the Christian Church.

01:08.972 --> 01:12.658
He puts it, as I'm showing you, in the form of a prophecy.

01:14.020 --> 01:20.550
And last Friday night we were drawing out some of the implications of that fact.

01:21.913 --> 01:25.658
Now then we can come therefore to the actual statement itself this evening.

01:26.840 --> 01:27.922
Here is a statement

01:28.258 --> 01:34.264
which is not only of great and vital importance, but one which is in many ways very difficult.

01:34.724 --> 01:42.732
And the result is, it has been the subject of much controversy, much difference and disagreement of opinion.

01:43.353 --> 01:52.101
Now, that is so for a number of reasons, the form in which the apostle puts it, I suppose, being the main reason for that.

01:53.222 --> 01:57.426
However, it deserves us therefore to examine it very carefully.

01:58.146 --> 02:06.899
and I trust we've all been praying together as I was trying to pray for you just now that we may be enlightened of the Spirit.

02:07.740 --> 02:09.122
It's such an important state.

02:10.785 --> 02:18.897
Now, the apostle gives his prophecy in the last part of verse 25 and the first part of verse 26.

02:19.979 --> 02:27.570
Then in the second of verse 26 and in verse 27 he supports it and substantiates it by quotations

02:27.746 --> 02:30.410
from the Old Testament.

02:30.430 --> 02:43.749
In other words, his following is usual method, makes his statement proves it confirms, shows that in a sense it is not a novelty, by means of his quotation from the Old Testament.

02:43.889 --> 02:46.032
Now here then it is the essential prophecy.

02:47.114 --> 02:55.826
The blindness in thought is happened to Israel, until the fullness of the Gentiles become in, and so

02:55.938 --> 02:58.081
All Israel shall be saved.

02:59.022 --> 02:59.863
That's the prophecy.

03:01.185 --> 03:03.048
And remember it is a prophecy.

03:04.410 --> 03:07.193
It is the revelation of a mystery.

03:08.055 --> 03:10.077
Something inaccessible to the mind of men.

03:10.878 --> 03:13.762
Something men can't foresee nor foretell.

03:14.664 --> 03:23.676
But something that has been revealed by God to his servant in order that he in term might make it known to others.

03:23.976 --> 03:25.298
And that's what he's doing here.

03:25.506 --> 03:27.268
He doesn't want them to be ignorant.

03:27.288 --> 03:38.524
He doesn't want them, as it were, eventually, to make fools of themselves by having said the wrong thing and then to be shown publicly to have said and thought the wrong thing.

03:39.084 --> 03:39.445
Very well.

03:39.885 --> 03:41.988
Now then, how do we approach this?

03:43.490 --> 03:46.374
There are two main ways in which a statement like this can be approached.

03:48.177 --> 03:55.026
One is, first and foremost, to give a general statement as to its meaning.

03:55.938 --> 04:00.344
and then support that by means of a detailed examination.

04:01.906 --> 04:05.211
That is the method that is adopted by Charles Hobbes, for instance, and others.

04:06.112 --> 04:08.876
But there's a second method, and to me it seems to be the preferable one.

04:09.877 --> 04:24.818
And it's this, that we first of all take the statement as it takes, break it up into its component parts, try to discover the meaning of the words and of the phrases, and then having got our exact detailed meaning

04:24.994 --> 04:29.540
we can then state the doctrine and argue concerning it.

04:30.161 --> 04:33.926
Consider the rival points of view and evaluate them together.

04:33.946 --> 04:35.789
It seems to me that that is the better procedure.

04:36.250 --> 04:43.840
So we've got to spend most of our time this evening, therefore, in what I would describe again as being the mechanics of interpretation.

04:44.922 --> 04:47.666
Let's see what the actual words are.

04:47.686 --> 04:49.769
Now, I commend this method for this reason.

04:50.750 --> 04:53.714
I think it's almost foolish to be

04:53.826 --> 05:01.016
having a general argument as to what the apostolic is saying, until we are quite clear in our minds as to what he is saying.

05:02.038 --> 05:12.692
It's foolish to take up the rival schools of thought with regard to the meaning of all Israel shall be saved, until we've examined the compartment parts of the whole great statement.

05:12.933 --> 05:14.956
Very well, so we start with the word blindness.

05:17.219 --> 05:19.622
This is the mystery that he is revealing to them.

05:21.505 --> 05:22.386
That blindness

05:24.162 --> 05:25.724
in thought has happened to Israel.

05:26.224 --> 05:31.369
Now, blindness is the word here in the authorized version that is before me.

05:32.110 --> 05:44.381
And in a sense, it is quite an accurate and a good translation, but the word that was used by the apostle does not mean blindness in and of itself.

05:44.401 --> 05:45.743
It means hardness.

05:47.364 --> 05:49.026
It means obtucious.

05:50.627 --> 05:53.330
It means insensibility.

05:53.986 --> 05:55.267
That's the root meaning.

05:55.868 --> 06:00.332
And of course, ultimately, therefore, it does come to mean blindness.

06:01.253 --> 06:03.916
If you're insensitive to truth, you can't see it.

06:04.796 --> 06:16.708
So, they were quite justified in using the word blindness, but as they have used hardness in other places, it seems to me that it would have been better if they had used hardness here.

06:17.189 --> 06:22.834
Now, there's nothing new about this statement to those of us who are familiar with this particular official.

06:23.010 --> 06:39.233
We really have this idea put before us in this same chapter already in verses 8, 9, and 10, where you read, according as it is written, God hath given them the spirit of slumber, eyes that they should not see and ears that they should not hear until this day.

06:39.694 --> 06:50.249
And David said that their table would be made a snare and a trap and a stumbling block and a recompense unto them, let their eyes be darkened that they may not see and bow down their back all the way.

06:50.269 --> 06:50.770
Same idea.

06:51.618 --> 06:59.890
And he's here putting it like this, that this blindness in part has happened to Israel.

07:00.471 --> 07:19.698
And of course, we've had the same essential idea in chapter 9, where you get it particularly in the 18th verse, where we read, therefore, hath he mercy on whom he will have mercy, and whom he will he heartless.

07:21.954 --> 07:31.351
Now, this is an idea that you get in descriptions that the trouble with the children of Israel was a hardness that led to blindness.

07:32.974 --> 07:38.503
And this, according to statements in the scripture, is ultimately the cause of unbelief.

07:39.886 --> 07:46.738
Take, for instance, the way in which the author of the Epistle to the Hebrews puts it in the third chapter, take verse 8.

07:47.874 --> 08:05.190
He says, oh, he's quoting, where far as the Holy Ghost says today, if you will hear his voice, harden not your house, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the wilderness, when your father's tempted me, proved me, and saw my works 40 years.

08:06.952 --> 08:11.957
So this man, the author of the Epistle to the Hebrews, makes an exhortation of all this.

08:12.017 --> 08:17.682
Take heed, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief.

08:18.050 --> 08:19.892
in departing from the living God.

08:21.153 --> 08:33.247
But exalt one another daily, while it is called today, lest any of you be hardened through the deceitfulness of sin.

08:33.267 --> 08:38.172
For we are made partakers of Christ if we hold the beginning of our confidence steadfast unto the end.

08:38.372 --> 08:47.122
And again the quotation, while it is said today, if you will hear his voice, hard not your heart, as in the provocation.

08:48.354 --> 08:53.801
Now that's the idea that is conveyed by this word, blindness.

08:53.821 --> 09:08.161
The trouble with Israel, the reason why the Jews as a nation rejected their own messiah and his teaching and rejected the teaching of the apostles and dealt to them in the cruel fashion they did was that they had become hardened.

09:08.181 --> 09:09.843
They'd become insensitive to truth.

09:10.604 --> 09:13.488
Truth could make no impression upon them.

09:13.508 --> 09:15.551
They've lost a sensibility.

09:16.933 --> 09:18.034
It's a terrible thing in this.

09:19.362 --> 09:24.928
And it is the ultimate explanation, as I say, of all unbelief.

09:24.948 --> 09:37.483
Now, in that third chapter of 2nd Corinthians that I was reading at the beginning, the apostles got the same idea, but there he puts it in terms of a veil over their hearts, so that they're not able to see.

09:37.503 --> 09:38.965
They've been blinded.

09:40.406 --> 09:43.910
This terrible inability to see the truth.

09:43.930 --> 09:46.994
Now, that's what he means by the word blindness.

09:48.354 --> 09:51.178
But then we come to this qualifying statement.

09:52.840 --> 09:57.927
He says that blindness in part is happened to Israel.

09:57.947 --> 09:59.489
What does he mean by in part?

10:00.751 --> 10:06.940
And here again, you see, there is obviously room for several different interpretations.

10:08.061 --> 10:10.985
Some people say that it means partial blindness.

10:11.926 --> 10:12.968
Partial blindness.

10:13.789 --> 10:17.394
That the Jews were not totally blind, but they were partially blind.

10:18.018 --> 10:22.343
that they still saw aspects of the truth, but they couldn't see it all.

10:22.863 --> 10:31.012
Now, this has got to be rejected completely, because the trouble with Israel was that she was totally blind.

10:32.294 --> 10:35.958
To reject them at Messiah means a total blindness.

10:37.179 --> 10:42.064
And that was the charge that our Lord so constantly brought against the very sins.

10:42.085 --> 10:47.090
They claimed that they had liked, that they were teachers of the people, that they were experts in the law.

10:47.522 --> 10:49.964
But the trouble was they were absolutely ignorant.

10:49.984 --> 10:51.125
It was a total blindness.

10:51.486 --> 10:53.708
Take the case of this apostle Paul himself.

10:54.329 --> 10:56.090
You remember how he went writing to Timothy?

10:57.071 --> 11:02.717
He refers to the days when he was a persecutor and a blasphemer and injurious.

11:03.257 --> 11:04.338
But you remember what he says?

11:04.638 --> 11:06.120
He says, I did it ignorantly.

11:06.620 --> 11:07.221
Ignorantly.

11:08.462 --> 11:09.103
In unbelief.

11:11.045 --> 11:13.867
It was nothing but ignorance, and it was a total ignorance.

11:13.887 --> 11:16.690
Or take the way he puts it in Philippians 3.

11:17.250 --> 11:20.955
where he gives the list of his excellencies as a Pharisee.

11:22.157 --> 11:25.561
As a Jew, an Hebrew, the Hebrew is his knowledge of the law and so on.

11:25.882 --> 11:31.249
But what he came to see was that he was totally ignorant of the true meaning of the law.

11:32.391 --> 11:40.562
It was a total blindness, not a partial blindness, and the trouble with Israel is not that he suffers from a partial blindness, it is a total blindness.

11:41.570 --> 11:47.598
then others would say that what it means is that blindness has happened to a part of Israel.

11:49.161 --> 11:52.345
But it isn't true of all of them, but only true of some of them.

11:52.365 --> 11:53.867
Well, of course, that was true.

11:54.708 --> 11:58.293
We've already seen in this chapter that the apostle makes that same point himself.

11:58.774 --> 12:04.702
He says, I am a believer, and not only that, he says there is a remnant according to the election of Greece.

12:05.684 --> 12:07.967
Some of the Jews have believed.

12:07.987 --> 12:10.130
So in a sense, it is true to say,

12:10.978 --> 12:20.188
that it was only some of the nation of Israel that were unable to see the truth of the gospel.

12:20.208 --> 12:35.584
And yet I am also going to reject that explanation of the meaning of this term, and I do so for this reason, that the apostle here is dealing not with individuals, but with the nation as a whole.

12:36.444 --> 12:37.906
Now I have to keep on saying,

12:38.882 --> 12:42.727
But in this chapter he is rarely dealing with the nation as a whole.

12:43.688 --> 12:49.135
The fact was that the nation as a whole was outside the church and it rejected the Messiah and the gospel.

12:49.355 --> 12:51.298
And he is here dealing with the nation as a whole.

12:51.618 --> 12:59.088
So I reject both those suggested explanations as to what he means by saying that blindness in part has happened to Israel.

12:59.368 --> 13:00.850
Well then what is he saying?

13:00.870 --> 13:02.292
Well it should be read like this.

13:03.914 --> 13:06.898
That blindness has happened in part to Israel.

13:08.482 --> 13:18.736
Not partial blindness has happened to Israel or blindness has happened to a part of Israel, but blindness has happened in part to Israel.

13:18.756 --> 13:19.457
What does that mean?

13:19.857 --> 13:30.652
Well, it means that he is referring to length of time, not the intensity of the blindness, but the duration of the blindness.

13:30.672 --> 13:32.715
So that a better way of translating this would be this.

13:33.416 --> 13:38.002
The blindness has happened temporarily to Israel.

13:38.370 --> 13:38.971
That's what he means.

13:39.892 --> 13:52.288
Blindness for the time being, a temporary blindness has happened to Israel, or blindness has happened temporarily to Israel.

13:52.689 --> 13:56.413
Now, what confirms that, of course, is the use of the word until.

13:57.555 --> 14:06.226
Blindness in thought is happened to Israel until the blindness is not permanent, it's not everlasting,

14:06.562 --> 14:08.344
It is a temporary blindness.

14:08.584 --> 14:10.045
That's what me means by impart.

14:10.426 --> 14:13.969
It is blindness has happened to Israel until.

14:15.030 --> 14:21.717
So it's a question of duration of the blindness and not the intensity of the blindness.

14:21.737 --> 14:29.424
Now, you see that when we come together up all these points, it will make the exposition, I think, quite inevitable.

14:29.844 --> 14:32.107
And my method of approach will be justified.

14:32.367 --> 14:35.730
But now we come to the next phrase, which is, is happen.

14:37.442 --> 14:41.989
You see, every single statement here, every phrase, every word is of great importance.

14:42.009 --> 14:49.962
Blindness in part is happened to Israel, which means, of course, has happened.

14:52.166 --> 14:53.969
Why do I pay attention to this?

14:54.309 --> 14:59.337
Is he saying any more than that Israel as a whole is blind?

15:01.721 --> 15:04.786
Well, obviously is, because if he only meant that, he just said that.

15:06.050 --> 15:14.499
When he says the blindness in thought has happened to Israel, he does mean that it is something that has happened to them.

15:14.519 --> 15:26.090
And that means this, that the blindness or the hardness to which he is referring is what we had to call when we were doing chapter 9, a judicial blindness.

15:28.433 --> 15:33.458
In other words, it isn't something that they produced themselves, it is something that has happened to them.

15:34.594 --> 15:36.576
something that has been put upon them.

15:36.596 --> 16:02.002
Now, the way, in other words, of interpreting this, is again to go back to chapter 9 and to read there what we read about God's dealings with Pharaoh, verse 17 and so on, for the Scripture says unto Pharaoh, even for this same purpose of I raise thee up, that I might show my power in thee, and that my name might be declared throughout all the earth.

16:02.242 --> 16:09.410
Therefore hath he mercy on whom he will have mercy and whom he will he harden up."

16:09.430 --> 16:11.092
You remember we dealt with that.

16:12.193 --> 16:13.114
You may not like that.

16:14.516 --> 16:15.557
Not a question of liking.

16:15.757 --> 16:16.478
I don't like it.

16:17.620 --> 16:20.403
But when you're reading the Scripture what matters is not what you like.

16:21.124 --> 16:21.904
Not what I like.

16:22.285 --> 16:23.266
It's what the Scripture says.

16:24.427 --> 16:26.710
Neither is it a matter of whether you can understand it or not.

16:27.451 --> 16:28.812
Who can understand such things?

16:29.113 --> 16:30.354
Paul says it's a mystery.

16:30.658 --> 16:35.183
And you remember the answer that he gave to the clever objector in chapter 9.

16:35.223 --> 16:45.373
Thou wilt say, then, unto me, why doth he yet find fault for who earth resisted his will, to which the answer is, nay, but, O men, who are thou that replyest against God?

16:46.754 --> 16:52.200
Shall the thing formed, say to him that formed it, why hast thou made me not?

16:52.220 --> 16:58.386
hath not the pot of power over the clay of the same lump, to make one desolate to honour and to honour and to dishonor?

16:59.650 --> 17:04.718
Now foolish it is for men to pit their little understandings against profound truth like this.

17:04.918 --> 17:06.060
Do you understand the miracle?

17:06.100 --> 17:09.105
Do you understand the rebirth?

17:10.507 --> 17:18.079
Well, if you think you do, you don't know what it is because our Lord told Nicodemus that it's a mystery, comparable only to the effect of the wind.

17:19.101 --> 17:22.446
Now, all not that I said unto thee, ye must be born again.

17:22.486 --> 17:27.634
The moment you take up this attitude of saying, I don't understand it and I don't like it,

17:28.610 --> 17:32.754
You as a Christian are putting yourself into the same position as an unbeliever.

17:33.315 --> 17:35.377
You're using exactly the same arguments.

17:36.619 --> 17:39.922
People don't believe in God because they can't understand the idea of a God.

17:40.363 --> 17:43.366
That's the typical unbeliever's argument.

17:43.746 --> 17:45.108
It's not what we understand.

17:45.128 --> 17:46.870
It is what has been revealed.

17:49.392 --> 17:54.578
And I'm saying this in order that I may remind you of what a serious thing it tells.

17:56.066 --> 18:04.497
to pit your understanding or your likes or dislikes against the word of the eternal and almighty God.

18:04.998 --> 18:09.464
Blindness in part has happened to Israel.

18:10.024 --> 18:12.608
It's been something that has been put upon them.

18:12.628 --> 18:23.602
Now, this doesn't mean that God is the author of unbelief, but what it does mean is this, that because of their unbelief and their persistence in it, he deliberately hardens them, as he did with fear.

18:23.970 --> 18:31.021
Now, all that has been stated already in verses 8, 9 and 10, which I've already read to you this evening.

18:31.442 --> 18:36.230
And of course, we've had it again in verses 11 and 12.

18:36.330 --> 18:38.653
I say them, have they stumbled that they should fall?

18:38.894 --> 18:39.535
God forbid.

18:39.935 --> 18:46.546
But rather, through their fall, salvation is come to the Gentiles,

18:46.850 --> 18:49.374
for to provoke them in the Jews to jealousy.

18:49.694 --> 18:55.523
Now if the fall of them be the riches of the world and the diminishing of them, the riches of the Gentiles, how much more they are fullness.

18:55.864 --> 19:02.093
God has chosen to do this to them in order to bring in the Gentiles and ultimately to provoke them to jealousy.

19:03.616 --> 19:15.634
But the point we are making therefore is this, that the part of the mystery is this, that God is inflicted upon the Jews as a hurlough, as a nation and as a race,

19:16.866 --> 19:19.529
this judicial blindness.

19:20.130 --> 19:26.217
Now, let me show you our Blessed Lord Himself rarely taught exactly the same thing.

19:26.677 --> 19:40.232
Do you remember what He says as it's recorded in the Gospel according to St. Matthew in chapter 13, as to why He spoke in parodies.

19:40.252 --> 19:40.813
Listen to this.

19:42.595 --> 19:45.298
Verse 10, and the disciples came and said unto Him,

19:45.378 --> 19:48.582
Why speakest thou unto them in parables?

19:49.683 --> 19:51.365
How often has this been misunderstood?

19:51.986 --> 19:56.711
I've heard, eventually, sometimes using the argument of parables in this way.

19:56.771 --> 20:00.675
They want to justify their own use of stories.

20:00.695 --> 20:01.717
They tell stories.

20:02.838 --> 20:05.261
And they justify this about our Lord told stories.

20:05.301 --> 20:06.582
Didn't he tell the parables?

20:06.862 --> 20:08.004
It's got to be made simple.

20:08.364 --> 20:11.167
They think that that is why our Lord spoke in parables.

20:12.028 --> 20:13.490
But listen to what he says himself.

20:13.794 --> 20:16.677
They ask him, why speakest thou unto them in parables?

20:17.198 --> 20:24.266
He answered and said unto them, because it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God.

20:24.786 --> 20:26.909
But to them it is not given.

20:28.150 --> 20:31.854
For whosoever hath to him shall be given, and he shall have more abundance.

20:32.515 --> 20:36.700
But whosoever have not, from him shall be taken away even that he hath.

20:37.160 --> 20:42.066
Therefore speak, I unto them in parable.

20:43.106 --> 20:47.374
because they seeing see not, and hearing they hear not.

20:47.794 --> 20:49.357
Neither do they understand.

20:49.417 --> 20:58.213
And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Esaius which says, by hearing, you shall hear and shall not understand.

20:58.894 --> 21:01.900
And seeing, you shall see and shall not perceive.

21:02.661 --> 21:05.426
For this people thought is wax gross.

21:05.538 --> 21:19.761
Same idea, that's the heartening again, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes of the closed list at any time they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them.

21:20.563 --> 21:24.910
But lesser do you arise for they see, and you are ears for they hear.

21:25.671 --> 21:32.402
For verily I say unto you that many prophets and righteous men have desired to see those things which ye see and have not seen them.

21:32.674 --> 21:35.657
and to hear those things which ye hear and have not heard.

21:35.697 --> 21:41.704
It's exactly the same thing as he says at the end of Matthew 11.

21:42.424 --> 21:58.802
I thank your father, Lord of him and earth, that thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and hast revealed them unto babe, even so father, for so it seemed good in thy sight.

21:59.102 --> 22:01.305
This is the deliberate action of God.

22:01.605 --> 22:02.546
He blinds

22:02.658 --> 22:19.196
He happens in a judicial manner, the race of the Jew, in order that he may not only punish them, but that he may bring his great purpose to the past, of sending the gospel to the Gentile and even ultimately through that to bring back the Jews as a whole.

22:19.397 --> 22:27.826
But this I say is an example, therefore, of judicial hardening or judicial blindness.

22:30.434 --> 22:34.238
Our Lord spoke in parables, less they might understand.

22:35.059 --> 22:40.063
He spoke in parables in order that they might not understand, and they didn't.

22:40.083 --> 22:46.830
They misunderstood completely, and that was because their hearts were hardened.

22:46.850 --> 22:50.854
Very well then, you see, the parable is this, as it is God doing flicks.

22:52.596 --> 22:59.122
This judicial blindness upon the june, it is God also who

22:59.778 --> 23:07.907
sometime in the future is going to open their eyes and restore and grab them in again.

23:08.428 --> 23:13.834
It is always God's action, both in the hardening and in the restoring.

23:13.854 --> 23:23.525
You notice the phrase in verse 26 of where he begins to quote, as it is written, there shall come out of Zion the deliverer.

23:25.427 --> 23:28.370
And remember it is the deliverer who shall

23:29.602 --> 23:32.185
turn away on godliness from Jacob.

23:33.046 --> 23:37.752
It isn't that Jacob of some future time is going to decide to believe.

23:38.593 --> 23:42.398
Now, the God who blinds is the God who heals.

23:43.659 --> 23:48.365
The God who casts out, breaks away the natural branches, is the same.

23:48.685 --> 23:50.287
God who is able to graph them in again.

23:50.607 --> 23:52.690
